WEBVTT

00:02.013 --> 00:03.480
I gotta get this hospital ready for

00:03.515 --> 00:05.049
the worst storm that we've seen in

00:05.083 --> 00:06.584
I don't know how many years.

00:06.618 --> 00:09.220
If you pull me off, won't I die?

00:09.254 --> 00:11.488
If we stay here, you definitely will.

00:13.625 --> 00:15.165
Get me a gurney!

00:16.027 --> 00:16.994
If people can't get to this hospital,

00:17.028 --> 00:19.330
then we need to bring
this hospital to them.

00:19.364 --> 00:20.497
Max, as your doctor,

00:20.532 --> 00:22.633
I cannot let you traipse through a storm.

00:22.667 --> 00:24.335
And I will take care of myself

00:24.369 --> 00:26.403
because I love my doctor.

00:26.438 --> 00:27.592
Honey, I'm sorry,

00:27.626 --> 00:30.040
but it's never gonna work out
between you and Max.

00:30.075 --> 00:31.175
We need to talk.

00:31.209 --> 00:33.853
This thing between us...

00:41.119 --> 00:42.353
Max.

00:42.387 --> 00:44.221
Uh, we lost power.

00:44.256 --> 00:45.518
Shouldn't the generator be coming on?

00:45.552 --> 00:46.691
Any second.

00:46.725 --> 00:48.359
What's happening?

00:48.393 --> 00:51.595
Um, sorry folks.
It appears we lost power,

00:51.630 --> 00:53.820
but the generator should
be kicking in shortly.

00:53.854 --> 00:54.965
Is everyone all right?

00:55.000 --> 00:57.301
My baby's cold. C4an I get a blanket?

00:57.335 --> 00:58.235
Newborn?

00:58.270 --> 00:59.970
My husband couldn't get here
for her birth,

01:00.005 --> 01:01.472
and we've been discharged.

01:01.506 --> 01:03.474
The insurance company
wouldn't let us stay.

01:03.508 --> 01:04.908
It's okay. Here, just take my coat,

01:04.943 --> 01:07.945
and I'll get you a blanket
as soon as possible.

01:07.979 --> 01:11.048
- Is the heat coming back on?
- Yeah, shortly.

01:11.082 --> 01:13.286
Come on in, guys.
Just head right over here.

01:13.321 --> 01:14.885
We're gonna fix this.

01:14.919 --> 01:16.954
- Max.
- Yeah?

01:16.988 --> 01:18.555
The generator should have
kicked in by now.

01:18.590 --> 01:20.257
The circulatory machines,
the ventilators...

01:20.292 --> 01:22.126
Okay, just do a quick status run,

01:22.160 --> 01:23.560
check all the wards,
and I'll meet you in the ED.

01:23.595 --> 01:25.562
- No... should someone else...
- I'm fine.

01:30.602 --> 01:32.910
You wanted to tell me something.

01:34.005 --> 01:35.606
It can wait.

